cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.CE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with communication over a fading channel and considers various cooperation techniques to improve the achievable rate. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also likely as the paper considers a network setting with colocated users and investigates the benefits of cooperation between them. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper deals with the design and analysis of a communication system with multiple layers and cooperation between users. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper considers the transmission of information from a single transmitter to a user. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is also a less likely category, but still possible as the paper involves mathematical modeling and analysis of the communication system.
